IgnanAlphabet: IgnanekRegions Spoken: Elemental Plane of FireDificulty: 2Language of fire creatures - Clerics of fire deities, Druids. Written form is Ignanek, a script based on Draconic. Ignan is a language of hissing percussive syllables, similar to the popping of a fire, and for a visitor to that plane might be mistaken for the natural sounds a fire will make. Those who speak it tend to speak quickly.It is spoken by most intelligent residents of the elemental plane of fire, and followers of deities who reside in that plane.It is based on Aragrakh, the ancient language of dragons who frequented the elemental planes of air and fire, and it's Iganek alphabet is loosely based on Draconic.